spec_data.Name: memstomp
spec_data.Description:
memstomp is a simple program that can be used to identify
places in code which trigger undefined behavior due to
overlapping memory arguments to certain library calls.
spec_data.Signature: RSA/SHA256, Fri 04 Aug 2017 04:58:28 PM EDT, Key ID f55e7430f5282ee4
spec_data.Summary: Warns of memory argument overlaps to various functions
